It has been reported that an undisclosed amount of money was taken from the wife of Baroka chairman Khurishi Mphahlele during a robbery at the club’s offices in Polokwane on Thursday. It is alleged that Mphahlele’s wife was robbed at gunpoint on her way back from the bank. Bakgaga CEO Morgan Mammila confirmed the incident to  KickOff.com. “It happened in one of our offices, I would prefer not to comment about the incident. It’s a sensitive matter,” he said. 